{"title_page": "Art of Living Foundation", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Advert|date=March 2013}}\n{{Primary sources|date=March 2013}}\n}}\n{{UPE|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name         =  The Art of Living Foundation\n|image        =  Art_of_Living_official_logo.png\n|headquarters = 21st Km, Udaypura, Kanakapura Road, [[Bengaluru]]\n|founder  = [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]]\n|website      = artofliving.org\n}}\n\nThe '''Art of Living Foundation''' is a volunteer-based, [[humanitarian]] and educational non-governmental organization (NGO).<ref>{{cite web|title=Art of Living Foundation|url=http://www.guidestar.org/organizations/77-0240101/art-living-foundation.aspx|publisher=GuideStar USA, Inc|accessdate=20 September 2013}}</ref> It was founded in 1981 by [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/profile/columnist/sri-sri-ravi-shankar/|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar|date=22 November 2018|website=The Indian Express|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref> The Art of Living Foundation has centers in more than 156 countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/education-today/gk-current-affairs/story/sri-sri-ravi-shankars-59th-birthday-10-interesting-facts-252655-2015-05-13|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar's 59th Birthday: 10 Interesting facts you shouldn't miss about him|date=13 May 2015|website=India Today|access-date=19 December 2018|first3=2015 12:51}}</ref> Art of Living offers several stress-elimination and self-development programs based on breathing techniques, meditation and yoga.\n\n== Organization ==\n[[File:Art of Living International Ashram.JPG|thumb|Art of Living International Centre in Bengaluru]]\nArt of Living Foundation has been an educational and humanitarian organization in the U.S. since 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esango.un.org/civilsociety/showProfileDetail.do?method=showProfileDetails&tab=3&profileCode=1291 |website=United Nations \u2013 Civil Society Participation |publisher=UN |accessdate=9 January 2019|title=United Nations Civil Society Participation (ICSO) \u2013 Login }}</ref> Accredited as a United Nations non-governmental organization in 1996, it works in special consultative status with the UN's Economic and Social Council, participating in a variety of committees and activities relating to health, education, sustainable development, conflict resolution, and disaster relief.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esango.un.org/civilsociety/consultativeStatusSummary.do?profileCode=1291 |website=United Nations \u2013 Civil Society Participation |publisher=UN |accessdate=9 January 2019|title=United Nations Civil Society Participation (ICSO) \u2013 Login }}</ref>\n\nThe majority of the officers of the organization, along with most of its teachers and staff, are volunteers.<ref>{{cite journal |title=AOL's volunteers |url=https://www.wired.com/1999/10/volunteers/ |journal=Wired|date=October 1999 }}</ref> Many humanitarian programs, disaster relief efforts, and training programs are conducted through, or in conjunction with a partner organization, the International Association for Human Values (IAHV).<ref name=\"iahv_sch\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-07-21/india/27994115_1_tsunami-free-education-school-compound|title=School for tsunami-affected children inaugurated in Tamil Nadu|date=21 July 2007|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=30 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Historical dictionary of new religious movements|last=1945\u2013|first=Chryssides, George D.|date=2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=9780810879676|edition=Second|location=Lanham, Md.|pages=75|oclc=828618014}}</ref> The organization is involved in community service through its centers, and programs are taken by people of many traditions and religious backgrounds. Its underlying principles are compatible with [[Advaita Vedanta|Vedic]] philosophy.<ref>Melton, J. Gordon (2003), ''Encyclopedia of American Religions'' (Seventh edition). Farmington Hills, Michigan: The Gale Group, Inc., p. 1004. {{ISBN|0-7876-6384-0}}</ref>\n\nSome of the key worldwide chapters include the Art of Living Foundation (U.S.A.), Vyakti Vikas Kendra (India), Die Kunst des Lebens (Germany), Art of Living Center (Canada), Art of Living South Africa, Art of Living Israel, Art of Living Brazil, and Art of Living Argentina. The Foundation operates as a charitable or a non-profit organization actively conducting \"Art of Living\" stress-relief courses, based on yoga, breathing, and meditation.<ref>Gautier, Francois. The Guru of Joy. New York: [[Hay House]], 2008.</ref>\n\nAccording to the tax return filed by the American chapter, AOL Foundation had total revenues of $US5.5 million, an income of $US3.5 million from course fees and expenditure of $US3.4 million from July 2006 to June 2007. Net assets at the beginning of July 2007 amounted to $US7.7 million.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.guidestar.org/FinDocuments//2007/770/240/2007-770240101-03db3e53-9.pdf |title=Art of Living Foundation, Fairfield, IA \u2013 Return of Organization Exempt from Income Tax, IRS 2006 |accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/77-0240101|title=Art of Living Foundation|website=GuideStar|access-date=19 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Programmes and courses==\n\nIts stress-elimination and self-development programs are based on the breathing technique [[Sudarshan Kriya]], meditation and yoga. This technique is a major part of Art of Living courses,<ref name=\"toi_course_firemen\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-04/mumbai/36741994_1_fire-station-pranayam-sudarshan-kriya|title=Pranayam lessons for Mumbai firemen|date=4 February 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=1 August 2013}}</ref> which are conducted by instructors, most of whom do voluntary work.<ref name=\"usf_students\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usforacle.com/usf-community-learns-the-art-of-living-1.2814809|title=USF community learns 'The Art of Living'|last=Naseer|first=Briana|date=4 March 2013|website=usforacle.com|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref> These courses have also been conducted for students and faculty,<ref name=\"usf_students\" /> government officials,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2003-06-14/mumbai/27173293_1_workshop-crime-branch-stress|title=30 state officials try to master Art of Living without stress|date=14 June 2003|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=1 August 2013}}</ref> firemen,<ref name=\"toi_course_firemen\" /> ex-militants,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-12/guwahati/31152597_1_ulfa-vocational-training-militants|title=Ex-rebels head for meditation courses|date=12 March 2012|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=1 August 2013}}</ref> and prisoners.<ref name=\"SA_prison\" />\n\n==Social service==\n\nIts areas of work cover conflict resolution,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/Sri-Sri-Ravi-Shankar-played-key-role-in-Colombian-peace-process/articleshow/54747177.cms|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar played key role in Colombian peace process|website=The Times of India|access-date=18 December 2018}}</ref> disaster and trauma relief,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/india-news/art-of-living-providing-trauma-relief-in-china_10056131.html |title=Art of Living providing trauma relief in China |publisher=Thaindian.com |date=3 June 2008 |accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/india-news/art-of-living-trauma-relief-through-broadcast-in-china_10056012.html |title=Art of Living trauma relief through broadcast in China |publisher=Thaindian.com |date=3 June 2008 |access-date=20 July 2010}}</ref> poverty alleviation, empowerment of women, prisoner rehabilitation,<ref name=SA_prison>{{cite news|title=South African prisoners embrace yoga|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/7777912.stm|publisher=BBC News|date=24 December 2008|first=Andrew|last=Walker}}</ref> education for all, and campaigns against female foeticide,<ref>{{cite news|title=Voices against female foeticide filed by: Nirmala|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-09-13/bangalore/28079205_1_female-foeticide-female-child-ratio-aol|work=The Times of India|date=13 September 2009}}</ref> child labour and for environmental sustainability.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAIL's CSR drive a boon for farmers|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-08-21/ranchi/28200321_1_icar-csr-drive-farmers|work=The Times of India|date=21 August 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"mge_100mil_pune\">{{cite news|title=AoL project to tackle global warming|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-03-14/pune/28016135_1_global-warming-aol-seeds|work=The Times of India|date=14 March 2009}}</ref>\n\n=== Project Vidarbha ===\nIn 2007, the foundation initiated the 'Project Vidarbha \u2013 'Swavalamban programme', with the aim of instructing and supporting farmers in severely drought hit regions to improve their living conditions. Over 1000 volunteers provided training in organic and [[Zero Budget Farming|zero-budget farming]], rainwater harvesting, hygiene, and the construction of toilets in addition to the Art of Living course.<ref>{{cite news|title=Art of Living rescues Vidarbha farmers|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/1088337/report-art-of-living-rescues-vidarbha-farmers|newspaper=DNA|date=2 April 2007}}</ref> The foundation received Rs 1.4&nbsp;million funding from the state Government against its total expenditure of nearly Rs 7.5&nbsp;million, some of which was self-financed, most of which was raised from corporate donors.<ref>{{cite web|title=After loan waiver, no Art of Living course for Vidarbha farmers|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/after-loan-waiver-no-art-of-living-course-for-vidarbha-farmers/327921/1|work=The Indian Express|date=27 June 2008}}</ref> A similar initiative was started to educate farmers in [[Andhra Pradesh]] to implement 'zero budget farming' to end suicides to due to financial stress.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sri Sri to help AP farmers|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-01-07/hyderabad/27745935_1_zero-budget-farming-state-farmers-religious-conversions|work=The Times of India|access-date=11 June 2013|date=7 January 2008}}</ref>\n\n=== Mission Green Earth ===\nIn partnership with [[United Nations Millennium Campaign]] and [[United Nations Environment Programme]] the 'Mission Green Earth Stand Up Take Action' campaign was launched in 2008 with a goal to plant 100 million trees across the world to help reduce global warming and protect the environment.<ref name=\"mge_100mil_pune\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Art of Living launches 'Mission Green Earth Stand Up Take Action'  |url=http://news.oneindia.in/2008/10/04/art-of-living-launches-mission-green-earth-stand-up-take-action-1223114635.html|publisher=news.oneindia.in|access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Students take up 'Mission Green Earth'|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/10/04/stories/2008100450970200.htm|work=The Hindu|access-date=11 June 2013|location=Chennai, India|date=4 October 2008}}</ref> In 2010, in Bangladesh the foundation participated in the 'Billion Tree Campaign' started by United Nations Environment Programme.<ref>{{cite web|title=Planting a billion trees|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=162343|work=The Daily Star|access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=News from the Campaign |url=http://www.plant-for-the-planet-billiontreecampaign.org/billiontreecampaign/CampaignNews/index.asp |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120513091021/http://www.plant-for-the-planet-billiontreecampaign.org/billiontreecampaign/CampaignNews/index.asp |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 May 2012 |publisher=United Nations Environment Programme |access-date=11 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\n=== River Rejuvenation Projects ===\nA three-year program to rejuvenate the [[Kumudavathi River]] (in Bangalore) was initiated by the foundation under its 'Volunteer for Better India' campaign in collaboration with civic authorities and environmentalists in February 2013.  \"The project aims to address the water shortage problems through rainwater harvesting, increasing green cover and de-silting existing step wells, among other methods.\" Volunteers join the villagers every Sunday to participate in these activities under guidance of a geological scientist.<ref name=\"TOI_Kumudvathi\">{{cite news|title=Art of Living initiates Kumudvathi River rejuvenation program|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-18/bangalore/37813379_1_river-basin-villages-water-scarcity|access-date=23 June 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=18 March 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"NIE_Kumudavathi_1\">{{cite news|title=Hoping for more water|url=http://newindianexpress.com/cities/bangalore/Hoping-for-more-water/2013/06/22/article1646640.ece|access-date=23 June 2013|newspaper=The New Indian Express|date=22 June 2013}}</ref> To create awareness about this program, Art of Living founder [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]],  joined by other NGOs, prominent citizens, civic authorities, farmers and volunteers led a walkathon in Bangalore City.<ref name=\"DNA_Kumudvathi_walkathon\">{{cite news|title=Kumudvathi revival plan draws citizens' interest|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bangalore/1845702/report-kumudvathi-revival-plan-draws-citizens-interest|accessdate=23 June 2013|newspaper=DNA|date=9 June 2013}}</ref> Apart from reviving some water bodies used by birds and animals,<ref>{{cite news|title=Ravi Shankar leads walkathon for water|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/ravi-shankar-leads-walkathon-for-water-113060800505_1.html|accessdate=23 June 2013|newspaper=Business Standard|date=8 June 2013}}</ref> the project had revived five water-recharge wells, constructed 74 boulder checks, cleaned up 18 step wells and planted 2,350 saplings in seven villages by June 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=He tames criminal instincts in jailbirds|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bangalore/He-tames-criminal-instincts-in-jailbirds/articleshow/36263869.cms|accessdate=25 June 2014|work=The Times of India|agency=TNN|date=9 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nSimilar efforts were held to revive [[Palar River|Pallar River]] in Andhra Pradesh, Manjra river in Maharashtra,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/reviving-water-bodies-is-an-art-of-living-now/articleshow/61945110.cms|title=Reviving water bodies is an Art of Living now|last=Basu|first=Ipsita|date=6 December 2017|work=The Economic Times|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>  and [[Vedavathi River]] in Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.downtoearth.org.in/blog/water/copying-nature-is-the-only-way-to-revive-our-rivers-57442|title=Copying nature is the only way to revive our rivers|website=downtoearth.org.in|access-date=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Volunteer For a Better India===\nThe Art of Living, combined with UN agencies, NGOs and civil society, launched Volunteer For a Better India (VFABI) on 5 December 2012. VFABI is involved in many activities, including protesting against the [[2012 Delhi gang-rape case]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-21/mumbai/35952963_1_vips-azad-maidan-silent-vigil|title=Mumbaikars hold public vigils to condemn Delhi horror; seek security for citizens, not VIPs|date=21 December 2012|work=The Times of India|access-date=19 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013, 1,634 volunteers distributed medicines worth Rs. 2.2&nbsp;million under the guidance of 262 doctors to over 20,000 slum dwellers in Delhi through 108 free health camps organized in collaboration with the [[Indian Medical Association]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Free health camps for slum dwellers by Art of Living|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/free-health-camps-for-slum-dwellers-by-art-of-living-113051000649_1.html|access-date=29 July 2013|newspaper=Business Standard|date=10 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, the 'I vote for better India' initiative was launched to increase awareness of the importance of voting as a responsibility towards the nation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Foundation urges citizens to vote|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Foundation-urges-citizens-to-vote/articleshow/24172020.cms|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=15 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=NGO volunteers enrol 35,000 people in voters' list|url=http://www.sakaaltimes.com/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsId=5179866745637335037&SectionId=5494605966908300850&SectionName=Civic&NewsDate=20131101&NewsTitle=NGO%20volunteers%20enrol%2035,000%20people%20in%20voters%E2%80%99%20list|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=Sakal Times|date=1 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=YCCE Supports 'I Vote For Better India' Campaign|url=http://www.nagpurtoday.in/ycce-supports-i-vote-for-better-india-campaign/|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=Nagpur Today|date=11 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n\n===Settlement with anonymous bloggers===\nIn 2010, Art of Living sued two anonymous bloggers, \"Skywalker\" and \"Klim\", accusing them of defamation, trade libel, copyright infringement and disclosing trade secrets, after they claimed to be former teachers/followers of the organisation and created blogs critical of Art of Living. The Foundation's request to unmask the bloggers' identities was denied, and the judge allowed only the trade secrets claim to go to trial.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.eastbayexpress.com/ebx/unmasking-the-art-of-living/Content?oid=3221659 | title = Unmasking The Art of Living | publisher = East Bay Express | date = 6 June 2010 | accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, a settlement was reached under which the foundation dropped the lawsuit without prejudice, compensated the bloggers' attorney fees, and agreed not to prosecute them, or any of their contributors.{{Better source|date=April 2013}} Skywalker and Klim agreed to freeze their existing blogs with no restriction on starting up new blogs critical of Art of Living.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eastbayexpress.com/92510/archives/2012/06/26/blogger-vs-alleged-cult-case-ends-in-favorable-settlement| title=Blogger vs. Alleged Cult Case Ends in Favorable Settlement | publisher=East Bay Express | date=26 June 2012| accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/art-living-foundation-v-does-1-10 | title=Art of Living Foundation v. Does 1\u201310 | publisher = Citizen Media Law Project}}</ref>\n\n===Land encroachment===\nIn 2011 a public-interest litigation petition was filed in the high court alleging that Art of Living had constructed structures encroaching upon the water spread area of Udipalya tank. The irrigation department of the state government of Karnataka inspected the area and found that the foundation had encroached<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Art-of-Living-Foundation-hints-at-moving-SC-against-NGT-order/article14388296.ece|title=Art of Living Foundation hints at moving SC against NGT order|date=6 June 2016|work=The Hindu|access-date=18 December 2018|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> upon {{Convert|6.53|hectare}} of the tank area and a show cause notice was issued to the foundation.<ref>{{cite news|title=AoL has encroached tank|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/article2719199.ece|work=The Hindu|access-date=17 February 2013|location=Chennai, India|date=16 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Sri Ravishankar grabs Rs 50 cr land illegally in K'taka?  |url=http://news.oneindia.in/2011/09/06/sri-sri-ravishankar-grabs-poors-land-illegally-for-aol.html|publisher=OneIndia News|access-date=17 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n===World Culture Festival on Yamuna flood plains===\nArt of Living Foundation organised [[World Cultural Festival|the World Culture Festival]] held on the [[Yamuna]] Flood plains in March 2016. A committee appointed by the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]] (NGT) recommended a fine of Rs 1,200 million on Art of Living Foundation for damaging the ecology of the flood plains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/02/28/art-of-living-fined_n_9340830.html|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar's Art Of Living Foundation Fined 120 Crore For Ecological Damage|date=28 February 2016|first=Piyasree|last=Dasgupta|website=huffingtonpost.in|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> The fine was reduced to Rs 50 million, with no further events to be allowed at that location.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/live-world-culture-festival-sri-sri-ravi-shankar-yamuna-parliament-rajya-sabha/|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar event gets NGT nod, Art of Living fined Rs 5 crore|date=10 March 2016|author=Express Web Desk|website=The Indian Express|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> After initially disputing the fine, [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]] declaring that he would rather go to prison,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Sri-Sri-Ravi-Shankar-Will-go-to-jail-but-wont-pay-Rs-5-crore-fine-NGT-fixes-deadline/articleshow/51353276.cms|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar: Will go to jail, but won't pay Rs 5 crore fine; NGT fixes deadline|author=TNN|date=11 March 2016|website=The Times of India|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> the foundation paid on 3 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/delhi/sri-sri-ravi-shankar-gives-pays-yamuna-fine-139|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar gives in, pays Yamuna fine|date=7 June 2017|website=asianage.com|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Burning of the Islamabad center in Pakistan ===\nAfter the organization's yoga center in [[Islamabad]], Pakistan was burned down by armed men in March 2014,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsweekpakistan.com/art-of-living-center-torched-in-islamabad/|title=Police Investigating If Yoga Center Was Targeted Due To Links To India And Founder Sri Sri Ravi Shankar.|date=10 March 2014|work=Newsweek|accessdate=25 June 2014|publisher=AG Publications|agency=Newsweek}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/did-pakistan-tv-debate-prompt-burning-yoga-center-n49036|title=Did Pakistan TV Debate Prompt Burning of Yoga Center?|date=10 March 2014|accessdate=25 June 2014|publisher=NBC News}}</ref> the Foundation reported receiving threats from the [[Taliban]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/news/article/Taliban-Threatens-Art-of-Living-Volunteers-in-Pakistan-AOL/844058|title=Taliban Threatens Art of Living Volunteers in Pakistan: AOL|work=Outlook|accessdate=25 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{coord|12.825845|77.508759|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Art of Living Foundation}}\n[[Category:Organisations based in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Spiritual organizations]]\n[[Category:Charities based in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{Advert|date=March 2013}}\n{{Primary sources|date=March 2013}}\n}}\n{{UPE|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name         =  The Art of Living Foundation\n|image        =  Art_of_Living_official_logo.png\n|headquarters = 21st Km, Udaypura, Kanakapura Road, [[Bengaluru]]\n|founder  = [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]]\n|website      = artofliving.org\n}}\n\nThe '''Art of Living Foundation''' is a volunteer-based, [[humanitarian]] and educational non-governmental organization (NGO).<ref>{{cite web|title=Art of Living Foundation|url=http://www.guidestar.org/organizations/77-0240101/art-living-foundation.aspx|publisher=GuideStar USA, Inc|accessdate=20 September 2013}}</ref> It was founded in 1981 by [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/profile/columnist/sri-sri-ravi-shankar/|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar|date=2018-11-22|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref> The Art of Living Foundation has centers in more than 156 countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/education-today/gk-current-affairs/story/sri-sri-ravi-shankars-59th-birthday-10-interesting-facts-252655-2015-05-13|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar's 59th Birthday: 10 Interesting facts you shouldn't miss about him|date=13 May 2015|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2018-12-19|first3=2015 12:51}}</ref> Art of Living offers several stress-elimination and self-development programs based on breathing techniques, meditation and yoga.\n\n== Organization ==\n[[File:Art of Living International Ashram.JPG|thumb|Art of Living International Centre in Bengaluru]]\nArt of Living Foundation has been an educational and humanitarian organization in the U.S. since 1989.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esango.un.org/civilsociety/showProfileDetail.do?method=showProfileDetails&tab=3&profileCode=1291 |website=United Nations - Civil Society Participation |publisher=UN |accessdate=9 January 2019|title=United Nations Civil Society Participation (ICSO) \u2013 Login }}</ref> Accredited as a United Nations non-governmental organization in 1996, it works in special consultative status with the UN's Economic and Social Council, participating in a variety of committees and activities relating to health, education, sustainable development, conflict resolution, and disaster relief.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://esango.un.org/civilsociety/consultativeStatusSummary.do?profileCode=1291 |website=United Nations - Civil Society Participation |publisher=UN |accessdate=9 January 2019|title=United Nations Civil Society Participation (ICSO) \u2013 Login }}</ref>\n\nThe majority of the officers of the organization, along with most of its teachers and staff, are volunteers.<ref>{{cite journal |title=AOL's volunteers |url=https://www.wired.com/1999/10/volunteers/ |journal=Wired|date=October 1999 }}</ref> Many humanitarian programs, disaster relief efforts, and training programs are conducted through, or in conjunction with a partner organization, the International Association for Human Values (IAHV).<ref name=\"iahv_sch\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-07-21/india/27994115_1_tsunami-free-education-school-compound|title=School for tsunami-affected children inaugurated in Tamil Nadu|date=21 Jul 2007|newspaper=THE TIMES OF INDIA|accessdate=30 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Historical dictionary of new religious movements|last=1945-|first=Chryssides, George D.|date=2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=9780810879676|edition=Second|location=Lanham, Md.|pages=75|oclc=828618014}}</ref> The organization is involved in community service through its centers, and programs are taken by people of many traditions and religious backgrounds. Its underlying principles are compatible with [[Advaita Vedanta|Vedic]] philosophy.<ref>Melton, J. Gordon (2003), ''Encyclopedia of American Religions'' (Seventh edition). Farmington Hills, Michigan: The Gale Group, Inc., p. 1004. {{ISBN|0-7876-6384-0}}</ref>\n\nSome of the key worldwide chapters include the Art of Living Foundation (U.S.A.), Vyakti Vikas Kendra (India), Die Kunst des Lebens (Germany), Art of Living Center (Canada), Art of Living South Africa, Art of Living Israel, Art of Living Brazil, and Art of Living Argentina. The Foundation operates as a charitable or a non-profit organization actively conducting \"Art of Living\" stress-relief courses, based on yoga, breathing, and meditation.<ref>Gautier, Francois. The Guru of Joy. New York: [[Hay House]], 2008.</ref>\n\nAccording to the tax return filed by the American chapter, AOL Foundation had total revenues of $US5.5 million, an income of $US3.5 million from course fees and expenditure of $US3.4 million from July 2006 to June 2007. Net assets at the beginning of July 2007 amounted to $US7.7 million.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://www.guidestar.org/FinDocuments//2007/770/240/2007-770240101-03db3e53-9.pdf |title=Art of Living Foundation, Fairfield, IA \u2013 Return of Organization Exempt from Income Tax, IRS 2006 |accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/77-0240101|title=Art of Living Foundation|website=GuideStar|access-date=2018-12-19}}</ref>\n\n==Programmes and courses==\n\nIts stress-elimination and self-development programs are based on the breathing technique [[Sudarshan Kriya]], meditation and yoga. This technique is a major part of Art of Living courses,<ref name=\"toi_course_firemen\">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-04/mumbai/36741994_1_fire-station-pranayam-sudarshan-kriya|title=Pranayam lessons for Mumbai firemen|date=4 February 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=1 August 2013}}</ref> which are conducted by instructors, most of whom do voluntary work.<ref name=\"usf_students\">{{cite web|url=http://www.usforacle.com/usf-community-learns-the-art-of-living-1.2814809#.UTR8oaDtGTY|title=USF community learns 'The Art of Living'|last=Naseer|first=Briana|date=4 March 2013|website=www.usforacle.com|access-date=26 April 2017}}</ref> These courses have also been conducted for students and faculty,<ref name=\"usf_students\" /> government officials,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2003-06-14/mumbai/27173293_1_workshop-crime-branch-stress|title=30 state officials try to master Art of Living without stress|date=14 June 2003|newspaper=The Times of India|accessdate=1 August 2013}}</ref> firemen,<ref name=\"toi_course_firemen\" /> ex-militants,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-03-12/guwahati/31152597_1_ulfa-vocational-training-militants|title=Ex-rebels head for meditation courses|date=12 Mar 2012|newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=1 August 2013}}</ref> and prisoners.<ref name=\"SA_prison\" />\n\n==Social service==\n\nIts areas of work cover conflict resolution,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/Sri-Sri-Ravi-Shankar-played-key-role-in-Colombian-peace-process/articleshow/54747177.cms|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar played key role in Colombian peace process - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2018-12-18}}</ref> disaster and trauma relief,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/india-news/art-of-living-providing-trauma-relief-in-china_10056131.html |title=Art of Living providing trauma relief in China |publisher=Thaindian.com |date=3 June 2008 |accessdate=20 July 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaindian.com/newsportal/india-news/art-of-living-trauma-relief-through-broadcast-in-china_10056012.html |title=Art of Living trauma relief through broadcast in China |publisher=Thaindian.com |date=3 June 2008 |access-date=20 July 2010}}</ref> poverty alleviation, empowerment of women, prisoner rehabilitation,<ref name=SA_prison>{{cite news|title=South African prisoners embrace yoga|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/7777912.stm|publisher=BBC News|date=24 December 2008|first=Andrew|last=Walker}}</ref> education for all, and campaigns against female foeticide,<ref>{{cite news|title=Voices against female foeticide filed by: Nirmala|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-09-13/bangalore/28079205_1_female-foeticide-female-child-ratio-aol|work=The Times of India|date=13 Sep 2009}}</ref> child labour and for environmental sustainability.<ref>{{cite news|title=SAIL's CSR drive a boon for farmers|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-08-21/ranchi/28200321_1_icar-csr-drive-farmers|work=The Times of India|date=21 August 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"mge_100mil_pune\">{{cite news|title=AoL project to tackle global warming|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-03-14/pune/28016135_1_global-warming-aol-seeds|work=The Times of India|date=14 Mar 2009}}</ref>\n\n=== Project Vidarbha ===\nIn 2007, the foundation initiated the 'Project Vidarbha - 'Swavalamban programme', with the aim of instructing and supporting farmers in severely drought hit regions to improve their living conditions. Over 1000 volunteers provided training in organic and [[Zero Budget Farming|zero-budget farming]], rainwater harvesting, hygiene, and the construction of toilets in addition to the Art of Living course.<ref>{{cite news|title=Art of Living rescues Vidarbha farmers|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/mumbai/1088337/report-art-of-living-rescues-vidarbha-farmers|newspaper=DNA|date=2 Apr 2007}}</ref> The foundation received Rs 1.4&nbsp;million funding from the state Government against its total expenditure of nearly Rs 7.5&nbsp;million, some of which was self-financed, most of which was raised from corporate donors.<ref>{{cite web|title=After loan waiver, no Art of Living course for Vidarbha farmers|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/after-loan-waiver-no-art-of-living-course-for-vidarbha-farmers/327921/1|work=The Indian Express|date=27 June 2008}}</ref> A similar initiative was started to educate farmers in [[Andhra Pradesh]] to implement 'zero budget farming' to end suicides to due to financial stress.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sri Sri to help AP farmers|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-01-07/hyderabad/27745935_1_zero-budget-farming-state-farmers-religious-conversions|work=Times of India|access-date=11 June 2013|date=7 January 2008}}</ref>\n\n=== Mission Green Earth ===\nIn partnership with [[United Nations Millennium Campaign]] and [[United Nations Environment Programme]] the 'Mission Green Earth Stand Up Take Action' campaign was launched in 2008 with a goal to plant 100 million trees across the world to help reduce global warming and protect the environment.<ref name=\"mge_100mil_pune\" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Art of Living launches 'Mission Green Earth Stand Up Take Action'  |url=http://news.oneindia.in/2008/10/04/art-of-living-launches-mission-green-earth-stand-up-take-action-1223114635.html|publisher=news.oneindia.in|access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Students take up 'Mission Green Earth'|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/10/04/stories/2008100450970200.htm|work=The Hindu|access-date=11 June 2013|location=Chennai, India|date=4 October 2008}}</ref> In 2010, in Bangladesh the foundation participated in the 'Billion Tree Campaign' started by United Nations Environment Programme.<ref>{{cite web|title=Planting a billion trees|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=162343|publisher=The Daily Star|access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=News from the Campaign |url=http://www.plant-for-the-planet-billiontreecampaign.org/billiontreecampaign/CampaignNews/index.asp |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120513091021/http://www.plant-for-the-planet-billiontreecampaign.org/billiontreecampaign/CampaignNews/index.asp |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 May 2012 |publisher=United Nations Environment Programme |access-date=11 June 2013 }}</ref>\n\n=== River Rejuvenation Projects ===\nA three-year program to rejuvenate the [[Kumudavathi River]] (in Bangalore) was initiated by the foundation under its 'Volunteer for Better India' campaign in collaboration with civic authorities and environmentalists in February 2013.  \"The project aims to address the water shortage problems through rainwater harvesting, increasing green cover and de-silting existing step wells, among other methods.\" Volunteers join the villagers every Sunday to participate in these activities under guidance of a geological scientist.<ref name=\"TOI_Kumudvathi\">{{cite news|title=Art of Living initiates Kumudvathi River rejuvenation program|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-18/bangalore/37813379_1_river-basin-villages-water-scarcity|access-date=23 June 2013|newspaper=Times of India|date=18 March 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"NIE_Kumudavathi_1\">{{cite news|title=Hoping for more water|url=http://newindianexpress.com/cities/bangalore/Hoping-for-more-water/2013/06/22/article1646640.ece|access-date=23 June 2013|newspaper=The New Indian Express|date=22 June 2013}}</ref> To create awareness about this program, Art of Living founder [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]],  joined by other NGOs, prominent citizens, civic authorities, farmers and volunteers led a walkathon in Bangalore City.<ref name=\"DNA_Kumudvathi_walkathon\">{{cite news|title=Kumudvathi revival plan draws citizens' interest|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bangalore/1845702/report-kumudvathi-revival-plan-draws-citizens-interest|accessdate=23 June 2013|newspaper=DNA|date=9 June 2013}}</ref> Apart from reviving some water bodies used by birds and animals,<ref>{{cite news|title=Ravi Shankar leads walkathon for water|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/ravi-shankar-leads-walkathon-for-water-113060800505_1.html|accessdate=23 June 2013|newspaper=Business Standard|date=8 June 2013}}</ref> the project had revived five water-recharge wells, constructed 74 boulder checks, cleaned up 18 step wells and planted 2,350 saplings in seven villages by June 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=He tames criminal instincts in jailbirds|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bangalore/He-tames-criminal-instincts-in-jailbirds/articleshow/36263869.cms|accessdate=25 June 2014|work=Times of India|agency=TNN|publisher=Times of India|date=9 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nSimilar efforts were held to revive [[Palar River|Pallar River]] in Andhra Pradesh, Manjra river in Maharashtra,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/reviving-water-bodies-is-an-art-of-living-now/articleshow/61945110.cms|title=Reviving water bodies is an Art of Living now|last=Basu|first=Ipsita|date=2017-12-06|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>  and [[Vedavathi River]] in Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.downtoearth.org.in/blog/water/copying-nature-is-the-only-way-to-revive-our-rivers-57442|title=Copying nature is the only way to revive our rivers|website=www.downtoearth.org.in|language=en|access-date=2018-12-17}}</ref>\n\n===Volunteer For a Better India===\nThe Art of Living, combined with UN agencies, NGOs and civil society, launched Volunteer For a Better India (VFABI) on 5 December 2012. VFABI is involved in many activities, including protesting against the [[2012 Delhi gang-rape case]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-12-21/mumbai/35952963_1_vips-azad-maidan-silent-vigil|title=Mumbaikars hold public vigils to condemn Delhi horror; seek security for citizens, not VIPs|last=|first=|date=21 December 2012|work=The Times Of India|access-date=19 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013, 1,634 volunteers distributed medicines worth Rs. 2.2&nbsp;million under the guidance of 262 doctors to over 20,000 slum dwellers in Delhi through 108 free health camps organized in collaboration with the [[Indian Medical Association]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Free health camps for slum dwellers by Art of Living|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/free-health-camps-for-slum-dwellers-by-art-of-living-113051000649_1.html|access-date=29 July 2013|newspaper=Business Standard|date=10 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, the 'I vote for better India' initiative was launched to increase awareness of the importance of voting as a responsibility towards the nation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Foundation urges citizens to vote|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Foundation-urges-citizens-to-vote/articleshow/24172020.cms|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=The Times of India|date=15 Oct 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=NGO volunteers enrol 35,000 people in voters' list|url=http://www.sakaaltimes.com/NewsDetails.aspx?NewsId=5179866745637335037&SectionId=5494605966908300850&SectionName=Civic&NewsDate=20131101&NewsTitle=NGO%20volunteers%20enrol%2035,000%20people%20in%20voters%E2%80%99%20list|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=Sakal Times|date=1 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=YCCE Supports \"I Vote For Better India\" Campaign|url=http://www.nagpurtoday.in/ycce-supports-i-vote-for-better-india-campaign/|access-date=28 November 2013|newspaper=Nagpur Today|date=11 Oct 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Controversies ==\n\n===Settlement with anonymous bloggers===\nIn 2010, Art of Living sued two anonymous bloggers, \"Skywalker\" and \"Klim\", accusing them of defamation, trade libel, copyright infringement and disclosing trade secrets, after they claimed to be former teachers/followers of the organisation and created blogs critical of Art of Living. The Foundation's request to unmask the bloggers' identities was denied, and the judge allowed only the trade secrets claim to go to trial.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.eastbayexpress.com/ebx/unmasking-the-art-of-living/Content?oid=3221659 | title = Unmasking The Art of Living | publisher = East Bay Express | date = 6 June 2010 | accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, a settlement was reached under which the foundation dropped the lawsuit without prejudice, compensated the bloggers' attorney fees, and agreed not to prosecute them, or any of their contributors.{{Better source|date=April 2013}} Skywalker and Klim agreed to freeze their existing blogs with no restriction on starting up new blogs critical of Art of Living.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eastbayexpress.com/92510/archives/2012/06/26/blogger-vs-alleged-cult-case-ends-in-favorable-settlement| title=Blogger vs. Alleged Cult Case Ends in Favorable Settlement | publisher=East Bay Express | date=26 June 2012| accessdate=7 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.citmedialaw.org/threats/art-living-foundation-v-does-1-10 | title=Art of Living Foundation v. Does 1-10 | publisher = Citizen Media Law Project}}</ref>\n\n===Land encroachment===\nIn 2011 a public-interest litigation petition was filed in the high court alleging that Art of Living had constructed structures encroaching upon the water spread area of Udipalya tank. The irrigation department of the state government of Karnataka inspected the area and found that the foundation had encroached<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/Art-of-Living-Foundation-hints-at-moving-SC-against-NGT-order/article14388296.ece|title=Art of Living Foundation hints at moving SC against NGT order|last=|first=|date=2016-06-06|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-12-18|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> upon {{Convert|6.53|hectare}} of the tank area and a show cause notice was issued to the foundation.<ref>{{cite news|title=AoL has encroached tank|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/article2719199.ece|work=The Hindu|access-date=17 February 2013|location=Chennai, India|date=16 December 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Sri Ravishankar grabs Rs 50 cr land illegally in K'taka?  |url=http://news.oneindia.in/2011/09/06/sri-sri-ravishankar-grabs-poors-land-illegally-for-aol.html|publisher=OneIndia News|access-date=17 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n===World Culture Festival on Yamuna flood plains===\nArt of Living Foundation organised [[World Cultural Festival|the World Culture Festival]] held on the [[Yamuna]] Flood plains in March 2016. A committee appointed by the [[National Green Tribunal Act|National Green Tribunal]] (NGT) recommended a fine of Rs 1,200 million on Art of Living Foundation for damaging the ecology of the flood plains.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.in/2016/02/28/art-of-living-fined_n_9340830.html|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar's Art Of Living Foundation Fined 120 Crore For Ecological Damage|date=28 February 2016|first=Piyasree|last=Dasgupta|website=www.huffingtonpost.in|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> The fine was reduced to Rs 50 million, with no further events to be allowed at that location.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/live-world-culture-festival-sri-sri-ravi-shankar-yamuna-parliament-rajya-sabha/|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar event gets NGT nod, Art of Living fined Rs 5 crore|date=10 March 2016|author=Express Web Desk|website=indianexpress.com|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> After initially disputing the fine, [[Ravi Shankar (spiritual leader)|Ravi Shankar]] declaring that he would rather go to prison,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Sri-Sri-Ravi-Shankar-Will-go-to-jail-but-wont-pay-Rs-5-crore-fine-NGT-fixes-deadline/articleshow/51353276.cms|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar: Will go to jail, but won't pay Rs 5 crore fine; NGT fixes deadline|author=TNN|date=11 March 2016|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref> the foundation paid on 3 June 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/delhi/sri-sri-ravi-shankar-gives-pays-yamuna-fine-139|title=Sri Sri Ravi Shankar gives in, pays Yamuna fine|date=7 June 2017|website=www.asianage.com|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Burning of the Islamabad center in Pakistan ===\nAfter the organization's yoga center in [[Islamabad]], Pakistan was burned down by armed men in March 2014,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsweekpakistan.com/art-of-living-center-torched-in-islamabad/|title=Police Investigating If Yoga Center Was Targeted Due To Links To India And Founder Sri Sri Ravi Shankar.|date=10 March 2014|work=Newsweek|accessdate=25 June 2014|publisher=AG Publications|agency=Newsweek}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/did-pakistan-tv-debate-prompt-burning-yoga-center-n49036|title=Did Pakistan TV Debate Prompt Burning of Yoga Center?|date=10 March 2014|accessdate=25 June 2014|publisher=NBC News}}</ref> the Foundation reported receiving threats from the [[Taliban]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.outlookindia.com/news/article/Taliban-Threatens-Art-of-Living-Volunteers-in-Pakistan-AOL/844058|title=Taliban Threatens Art of Living Volunteers in Pakistan: AOL|publisher=Outlook|accessdate=25 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{coord|12.825845|77.508759|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Art of Living Foundation}}\n[[Category:Organisations based in Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Spiritual organizations]]\n[[Category:Charities based in India]]\n", "name_user": "Dawnseeker2000", "label": "safe", "comment": "fixeddashesusing ascript, date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript,Script-assisted fixes: perCS1andMOS:ITALICS", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Art_of_Living_Foundation"}
